Preheat the #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve the @lemon{1}. Cut half into thick wedges and juice the rest.

Chop the @tomato{2} into small pieces.

Trim and grate the @carrot{1}(trimmed and grated, no need to peel). Trim and
thinly slice the @scallion{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced).

In a #bowl, mix the tomato with half the scallion then season with @salt{to taste},
@pepper{to taste} and 1 tsp lemon juice (double for 4p).

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the @diced Irish chicken breast{260%grams} and season with salt and
pepper.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.
Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due
to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

Once the chicken is cooked, add @ground cumin{1%sachet}, @ketchup{1%sachet} and
half the grated carrot to the pan.

Cook until the carrot is tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove from the heat. Stir through the @chipotle paste{1%sachet}.

Season to taste with salt, pepper and @sugar{to taste}.

Lay the @tortilla{8} out on a #board, spoon some of the chicken filling down the
centre of each, then roll up to enclose.

Drizzle a little oil into the bottom of an #ovenproof dish{} and lay in the
enchiladas.

Pack them snugly, side by side, with the folded edge underneath so they don't
unroll.

Top with the @grated cheese{50%grams}.

Bake on the top shelf of your #oven until the cheese is melted, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @avocado{1} and scoop the flesh into a #bowl.

Mash with a #fork and add a squeeze of lemon juice.

Season to taste salt and pepper then mix well to combine.

Once cooked, remove the enchiladas from the #oven.

Divide between #plates.

Top with the smashed avocado.

Serve with tomato salsa, remaining carrot and lemon wedges alongside.

Garnish with a sprinkling of the remaining scallion.